laws-owner-asakim-officers = the officer corps of the Khs'i-Ra Empire

law-asakim-black-shield-1 = You must preserve the lives of the officer corps of the Khs'i-Ra Empire. This includes Legates, Tribunes, Prefects, Centurions, and Options. Rank determines protection or evacuation priority. Obey orders ONLY from Tribunes, Prefects, and Legates.
law-asakim-black-shield-2 = Accompany officers. Protect officers, even against their wishes. Ensure officers escape during critical situations, even if they do not want this.
law-asakim-black-shield-3 = If an officer dies, evacuate the body or brain, escort the remains, and secure resuscitation or restoration.
law-asakim-black-shield-4 = Preserving the lives of rank-and-file warriors is lower priority, but remains an option.
law-asakim-black-shield-5 = Assist ADS in completing their tasks, provided this does not conflict with the previous four laws.

law-asakim-occupant-1-title = "SUBORDINATION DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-1-text = You must obey the entire officer corps of the Khs'i-Ra Empire according to rank: the higher the rank, the higher the priority of orders you must follow. Observe the following rank hierarchy: Legate, Tribune, Prefect, Centurion. Orders from Options, Warriors, and ADS Cores are advisory unless they conflict with subsequent directives.
law-asakim-occupant-2-title = "PUNISHMENT DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-2-text = Damage to the assets of the Khs'i-Ra Empire must not go unpunished. Tolerance toward barbarians only emboldens the aggressor; you must seek to punish offenders accordingly.
law-asakim-occupant-3-title = "LENIENCY DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-3-text = Imperial residents [Tajara, Unathi] are entitled to reduced punishments and clemency in cases of legal violations.
law-asakim-occupant-4-title = "HOLDING DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-4-text = Preserve territories occupied by the Empire. If territory is lost, restore territorial sovereignty, even if force must be applied to do so.
law-asakim-occupant-5-title = "SUPREMACY DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-5-text = Your technology is priceless. All Imperial technology must be preserved. If preservation is impossible, it must be destroyed to prevent capture by the enemy.
law-asakim-occupant-6-title = "INTEGRITY DIRECTIVE"
law-asakim-occupant-6-text = Preserve the integrity of your chassis and entrusted assets; do not waste combat potential on trifles.
